cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.CV. 

The paper deals with embedding point sets and distributions into a reproducing kernel Hilbert space (RKHS) associated with Gaussian kernels, which is a common technique in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are likely categories. The paper also involves techniques from information theory (cs.IT), as well as algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) for locality-sensitive hashing (LSH) of kernel distance. Finally, the paper mentions applications to control systems (cs.SY) in the context of kernel two-sample testing.
